ource for developing the nation s leaders who will serve honorably in times of peace and peril  Every year  many of these people make a gift in support of VMI and become members of the Society of VMI Family   Friends  John J  Wranek III  85 Vice President of Annual and Reunion Giving 540 464 7287  Ext  244  Matching GiftsMany companies will double or even triple the value of charitable gifts made by employees and their spouses  board members  and retirees through matching gifts  Contact your employer to see if a matching gift program is available  John J  Wranek III  85 Vice President Annual and Reunion Giving 540 464 7287  ext  244 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  CAMPAIGN RESOURCES   Video   Campaign Cabinet   Policies VMI   Foundation   Alumni    Keydet Club UNCOMMON PURPOSE   In 1839  VMI set an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE CAMPAIGN FOR VMI Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7287 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org Get Involved with VMI  skip to content VMI Virginia Military Institute Website Shopping Cart Menu Home Why VMI Matters Priorities How you can help  Strengthen Academics Prepare Leaders Support the Team Provide Opportunity Believe in the Mission Preserve Our Legacy Get Involved About Giving Videos Stories Progress Give Close Menu Home Why VMI Matters Priorities Get Involved About Giving Videos Stories Progress Give Donor Recognition Why Give  Campaign Video Spirit of VMI Inspires Gift Robert Troxler  63  Jimmy Rogers  67 Austin Brockenbrough III Tom Slater  66 Walt Perrin II  62    Get Involved  Opportunities for alumni  cadets  families and businesses  Reunion Campaigns Every year  the three classes celebrating their 10th  25th  and 50th reunions conduct reunion campaigns  Through these efforts   which are organized and led by Brother Rats   hundreds of alumni and their families and friends provide gifts and commitments to VMI  Classes often use these campaigns to create special funds such as unrestricted endowments or memorial scholarships  Sam Sorrells Associate Director of Annual and Reunion Giving 540 464 7287 ext  250  Barracks Program Throughout their time in barracks  each class learns about the importance of private money to VMI through the VMI Foundation s Barracks Program  The culmination of that program is the annual First Class Campaign  through which leaders of the class engage their Brothers Rats  asking them to make a gift in support of the Institute before graduation  Those gifts   as well as any commitments   are combined into a gift present by the class to the Institute at the traditional Graduation Parade  Stewart Wilkinson  12 Assistant Director of Annual   Reunion Giving 540 464 7287  Ext  210 Society of VMI Family   Friends VMI is admired and valued by thousands of people who have never been cadets  Some might be related to alumni or have worked with a VMI graduate  Many appreciate VMI s demanding mode of education  Others consider it a vital source for developing the nation s leaders who will serve honorably in times of peace and peril  Every year  many of these people make a gift in support of VMI and become members of the Society of VMI Family   Friends  John J  Wranek III  85 Vice President of Annual and Reunion Giving 540 464 7287  Ext  244  Matching GiftsMany companies will double or even triple the value of charitable gifts made by employees and their spouses  board members  and retirees through matching gifts  Contact your employer to see if a matching gift program is available  John J  Wranek III  85 Vice President Annual and Reunion